<doc id="145721" wikidata="Q866849" url="?curid=145721" title="North Jutland County">
<text>North Jutland County () is a former county (Danish: &quot;amt&quot;) in northern Denmark. It was located on the eastern half of Vendsyssel-Thy and the northernmost part of the Jutland peninsula. It was the largest county in Denmark, but with a relatively low population. The county seat was Aalborg, Denmark&#x27;s fourth largest city. The county was abolished effective January 1, 2007, when it merged into North Denmark Region ().

